import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['normal'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['normal'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperatures in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['normal'], alpha=0.5, label='Normal')
    ax.hist(data['actual'], alpha=0.5, label='Actual')
    ax.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', label='Normal Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['actual'].mean(), color='green', label='Actual Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('How does the distribution of actual temperatures compare to the distribution of normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = data['actual'] - data['normal']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['difference'], vert=False)
    ax.axvline(data['difference'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['difference'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average difference between normal and actual temperatures?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'])
    plt.title('How does the distribution of actual temperatures vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.scatter(data['day'], data['actual'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the date of the weather record and the actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date of Weather Record')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    return plt;
